gin-left: 0.5in; text-indent: -0.25in; line-height: 80%;" class="MsoNormal"><!--[if !supportLists]--><span style="font-size: 12pt; line-height: 80%;"><span style="">1)<span style="font: 7pt &quot;Times New Roman&quot;;">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span><!--[endif]--><span style="font-size: 12pt; line-height: 80%;">An Interpreted Language : JavaScript is an interpreted language, which requires no compilation steps. This provide an easy development process. The syntax is completely interpreted by the browser just as a interprets html tags.<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n<p style="margin-left: 0.5in; text-indent: -0.25in; line-height: 80%;" class="MsoNormal"><!--[if !supportLists]--><span style="font-size: 12pt; line-height: 80%;"><span style="">2)<span style="font: 7pt &quot;Times New Roman&quot;;">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span><!--[endif]--><span style="font-size: 12pt; line-height: 80%;">Embedded within html : JavaScript doesn&rsquo;t requires any special or separate editor for programs to be written, edited or complied. It can written in any text editor like<span style="">&nbsp; </span>Notepad, Dreamweaver along with appropriate html tags and saved as filename.html<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n<p style="margin-left: 0.5in; text-indent: -0.25in; line-height: 80%;" class="MsoNormal"><!--[if !supportLists]--><span style="font-size: 12pt; line-height: 80%;"><span style="">3)<span style="font: 7pt &quot;Times New Roman&quot;;">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span><!--[endif]--><span style="font-size: 12pt; line-height: 80%;">Minimal syntax easy to learn: By learning just a few commands and simple rules of syntax, complete applications can be built using JavaScript.<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n<p style="margin-left: 0.5in; text-indent: -0.25in; line-height: 80%;" class="MsoNormal"><!--[if !supportLists]--><span style="font-size: 12pt; line-height: 80%;"><span style="">4)<span style="font: 7pt &quot;Times New Roman&quot;;">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span><!--[endif]--><span style="font-size: 12pt; line-height: 80%;">Quick Development: Because JavaScript doesn&rsquo;t require time-consuming compilations, script can be developed in a short period of time.<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n<p style="margin-left: 0.5in; text-indent: -0.25in; line-height: 80%;" class="MsoNormal"><!--[if !supportLists]--><span style="font-size: 12pt; line-height: 80%;"><span style="">5)<span style="font: 7pt &quot;Times New Roman&quot;;">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span><!--[endif]--><span style="font-size: 12pt; line-height: 80%;">Performance: JavaScript can be written such that the html files are fairly compact and quite small. This minimizes storage requirements on the web server and downloads time for the client.<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n<p style="margin-left: 0.5in; text-indent: -0.25in; line-height: 80%;" class="MsoNormal"><!--[if !supportLists]--><span style="font-size: 12pt; line-height: 80%;"><span style="">6)<span style="font: 7pt &quot;Times New Roman&quot;;">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span><!--[endif]--><span style="font-size: 12pt; line-height: 80%;">Procedural capabilities: Every programming language needs to support facilities such as condition checking looping and branching. JavaScript also provides such procedural capabilities.<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n<p style="margin-left: 0.5in; text-indent: -0.25in; line-height: 80%;" class="MsoNormal"><!--[if !supportLists]--><span style="font-size: 12pt; line-height: 80%;"><span style="">7)<span style="font: 7pt &quot;Times New Roman&quot;;">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span><!--[endif]--><span style="font-size: 12pt; line-height: 80%;">Designed for programming user Events: JavaScript supports object/event based programming. JavaScript recognizes when a form button is pressed. It also help in recognizing a mouse events like mouse up, mouse move, mouse down. onclick , onsubmit.<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n<p style="margin-left: 0.5in; text-indent: -0.25in; line-height: 80%;" class="MsoNormal"><!--[if !supportLists]--><span style="font-size: 12pt; line-height: 80%;"><span style="">8)<span style="font: 7pt &quot;Times New Roman&quot;;">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span><!--[endif]--><span style="font-size: 12pt; line-height: 80%;">Easy Debugging and Testing : Being an interpreted language, scripts in javaScript are tested as line by line and the errors are also<span style="">&nbsp; </span>listed as they are encounterd.<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n<p style="margin-left: 0.5in; text-indent: -0.25in; line-height: 80%;" class="MsoNormal"><!--[if !supportLists]--><span style="font-size: 12pt; line-height: 80%;"><span style="">9)<span style="font: 7pt &quot;Times New Roman&quot;;">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span><!--[endif]--><span style="font-size: 12pt; line-height: 80%;">Platform Independence Architecture Neutral : JavaScript is a programming language that is completely independent of the hardware on which it works. It is a language that is understood by any javascript enabled browser.<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n</p>', '2011-04-13', 'Naresh', 0x31);
